dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: Lambert conical orthomorphic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by contours, gradient tints, and spot heights.  Five classes of roads and four classes of railroads are shown.  Covers area north from Berlinchen [Barlinek, Poland] to Rothenburg a. O. [Czerwieńsk, Poland] to the south, and west from Seelow [Germany] to Pinne (Pniewy) [Poland] to the east. Frankfurt am Oder [Frankfurt an der Oder, Germany] roughly below left center portion of sheet.  Sheet O 53, Frankfurt-am-Oder from set that includes various issues of some sheets, some by various survey units of the Allied Forces (A.F.) some reissued by U.S. Army Map Service, some sheets, G.S.G.S. 4346; some sheets A.M.S. M508 (G.S.G.S. 4346).  Heights in metres..  Certain main spot heights are indicated by a white tab to improve legibility..  Military grid.  Spheroid: Du Plessis..  Cataloging agency's copy printed on verso of portion of unrelated German map sheet, Blatt Nr. 85, Hawick und Eskdale, from series with title: Schottland 1:50 000, originally published [Berlin?] : [Abteilung für Kriegskarten- und Vermessungswesen II], 1941- German series consists of enlargements, for the use of the German Army, from the Ordnance Survey Popular Edition one-inch maps (1:63,360) from sheets issued between 1924 and 1932.  IXA.  Includes Convergence for corners of this sheet, To give a grid reference on this sheet, Index to adjoining sheets, Grid data, Conversion table, Glossary, Authorities, and Incidence of grid letters.
dct_isPartOf_sm: Field Maps of Colonel Roland T. Fenton
